JavaDoc
-----------------

Ignore JavaDoc : 
	<plugin>
				<groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
				<artifactId>maven-javadoc-plugin</artifactId>
				<executions>
					<execution>
						<id>attach-javadocs</id>
						<goals>
							<goal>jar</goal>
						</goals>
					</execution>
				</executions>
				<configuration>
					<additionalOptions>
						<additionalOption>-Xdoclint:none</additionalOption>
					</additionalOptions>
				</configuration>
			</plugin>
mvn clean install -Dmaven.javadoc.skip=true

Git commands (SCM and VC tool)
=====================================
(local repository = staging area =  .git folder inside the workspace)
git init
git checkout -b test (new branch)
git checkout master (switch to existing branch)
git pull origin master
                    Local Repository
        -> git fetch                        -> git merge
Remote Repository      ------> git pull              Workspace

git commit -m "initial commit"
git clone <repository-url>
git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git branch
git stash
git stash pop
git reset --soft HEAD~1 (to remove if committed to master directly)

Git Merge
================
git merge feature main

main branch commits are put into feature branch
safe :: existing branches are not changed

Git Rebase
================
git rebase feature main

feature branch commits are put into main - each commit in feature is a commit in main
cleaner project history

The golden rule of rebasing :: only use if no one else is working on the main branch


You have not concluded your merge (MERGE_HEAD exists). Please, commit your changes before you merge
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
git merge --abort
git reset --merge
Pull the branch and resolve the conflicts



